LAGOS – PremiumTrust Bank in fulfilling its brand promise of partnering for growth has stated that it will play a major role at the 21st National Sports Festival (NSF) billed for Asaba, Delta State from November 2 to 15, 2022. The Managing Director of PremiumTrust Bank, Mr Emmanuel Emefienim reiterated the Bank’s commitment to growth, impacting lives and communities. He also highlighted that as the official Banker of the National Sports Festival, already tagged: ‘Delta 2022’, the bank aims to contribute to the development of sports in Nigeria and foster unity in our diversity as a nation. “In partnership with the National Sports Festival (NSF), Premium Trust Bank is committed to providing the needed platform to help athletes grow and excel in their chosen fields consistent with our tag line – “Together for Growth”. He called on the youths to take advantage of the platform provided by this Sports Festival in their pursuit of excellence both within the country and at the international stage in sports. It will be recalled that on Wednesday, July 6, 2022 Emefienim joined the Delta State Government and the Hon. Minister for Youths and Sports Development at the Government House in Asaba, to unveil the official mascot and logo of the 21st NSF. The NSF since its inception in 1973 is being hosted for the very first time in Asaba, Delta State. Minister of Youths and Sports Development, Mr Sunday Dare, Delta State State Governor Ifeanyi Okowa, and Managing Director, Premium Trust Bank, Mr. Emmanuel Emefienim as well as other top government functionaries and dignitaries were in attendance at the unveiling of the event’s logo and Mascot in Asaba. Governor Okowa, in his words, described the National Sports Festival as Nigeria’s version of the Olympic Games and declared that Delta State will make it an unforgettable experience for everyone.